Patch Set 13:

Do we want to trust that we don't hit this anywhere else if we just change the behavior only in the filters? Personally I think the sanitizer is good place to clean the input to the json at single location, after all that's why it is there. Specifically when the content seems to change depending of the webob version (1.1.1-uubuntu0 for example returns UnicodeMultiDict where the 1.2.3 returns MultiDict, what future versions will return, we do not know and it's used quite widely).
